body:
Given the following code for a package called `mypackage`: 

in the `src/main.rs`:
```rust
fn main() {
    println!("Hello, world!");
}

pub fn test_stuff() -> u32 {
    42
}
```
in an example at `examples/example1.rs`:
```rust
extern crate mypackage;
use mypackage::test::test_stuff();

fn main(){
    println!("Hello World!");
}
```
in another example at `examples/example2.rs`:
```rust
use mypackage::test::test_stuff();

fn main(){
    println!("Hello World!");
}
```


The current output is (I used keep going just to get everything in one command):

```
$ cargo build -Z unstable-options  --keep-going --examples
   Compiling mypackage v0.1.0 (/home/caspar/.local/share/temp/2022-12-05-11-14)
error[E0463]: can't find crate for `mypackage`
 --> examples/example1.rs:1:1
  |
1 | extern crate mypackage;
  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ can't find crate

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0463`.
error: could not compile `mypackage` due to previous error
warning: build failed, waiting for other jobs to finish...
error[E0432]: unresolved import `mypackage`
 --> examples/example2.rs:1:5
  |
1 | use mypackage::test;
  |     ^^^^^^^^^ use of undeclared crate or module `mypackage`

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0432`.
error: could not compile `mypackage` due to previous error
```

Ideally the output should mention that a lib.rs is required and that it can only find a main.rs.

I'd suggest the note to be this:
```
Note: The package mypackage does not contain a lib.rs file to be imported. Package imports only use the items exposed by the lib.rs and ignore the main.rs file.
```
